ction to this game, and Iam only at level 4!!!<br><br>Please help if you can, I really want to play this game, thanks  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utandaina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tandaina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/31/02 12:04:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAOC crashing with Nvidia card, tried most solutions.</span><hr size=1> Ok, follow these steps:<br><br>First make sure you have a good solid DX release.  Not sure what others would recommend but I'm using 8 and it works fine for me.<br><br>Download the most recent drivers for your MOTHERBOARD. (I never knew to do this till recently).  4-in-1, AGP, etc.<br><br>Download the MOST recent vid card drivers from NVidia.<br><br>Install MB drivers, then NVidia drivers being sure to first remove the old ones.  (though looks like the newest driver installers do this for you.)<br><br>Now try the game again.<br><br>Whenever I get problems with 3D apps the first place I look is upgrading my MB and Vid card drivers together.  Could also need new sound card drivers. So check on those. <p>Silverleaf Goldenthorn - Warden of Connla<BR>Goldenrod - Enchanter<BR>Ivey - Ranger</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upakaraatzi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pakaraatzi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/31/02 2:36:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAOC crashing with Nvidia card, tried most solutions.</span><hr size=1> Yep, like I said, I've tried all those solutions, and NONE fix it.<br><br>I've been reading forums, and tech support docs for the last 2 days now, I've found all the solutions you mentioned, tried over and over, and it just keeps crashing.  I've e-mailed the company, but havnt got a response yet. :( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/1/02 12:25:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/rtfm.txt width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAOC crashing with Nvidia card, tried most solutions.</span><hr size=1> Pakaraatzi says:  <b><i>Ok, I got DAOC yesterday, but I cant play it for more then 15 minutes before it crashes either to the desktop, or to a BSOD.</b></i><br><br>What is the exact message of the BSOD?  In particular, what executable does it list as causing the error (i.e., ntkernel, nv_disp4.dll, etc.)?<br><br>This may not be a display driver issue at all.  The only driver revision which I know has problems with DAOC is 21.83.  The 23.11s (latest on Nvidia's official site) should work just fine.<br><br>Some preliminary things you want to check:<ul><li>Do you have your latest motherboard drivers?</li><br><li>Did you install DirectX 8.1 from Microsoft?</li><br><li>Are your network/display/sound cards sharing an IRQ, through ACPI or otherwise?</li><br><li>Are your sound card drivers updated?</li><br><li>Are you using an SB Live! (in which case, do yourself a favor and toss it out the window)?</ul>More information about your setup (motherboard type, nature of error, types of PCI cards installed) would be helpful. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A> at: 1/31/02 9:25:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upakaraatzi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pakaraatzi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/1/02 3:23:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAOC crashing with Nvidia card, tried most solutions.</span><hr size=1> I didn't read the <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroveboardpostingrulesandpolicy.showMessage?topicID=1.topic>rules</a> so I said a bunch of mean things that are not allowed. Please forgive my trollish outburst.<br><br><i>obviously edited for content by your favorite Druish Princess</I> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaliciaswiftfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salicia Swiftfoot</A> at: 2/4/02 10:10:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utandaina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tandaina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/1/02 8:13:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAOC crashing with Nvidia card, tried most solutions.</span><hr size=1> Uh huh.  Yeah that is NOT going to get you help.  Sorry no more free tech support for me.<br><br>Tud does NOT deserve that response. <p>Silverleaf Goldenthorn - Warden of Connla<BR>Goldenrod - Enchanter<B